reason.tex:
%text
 $f(x) = f:\N\to\N$. Which means that $f(x)$ is defined \underline\text{only for $x\in\N$}
 Hence, $f(x)$ is defined for $x=1,2,3,\ldots\infty$. But it is not defined for $x=1.5$ or $x=100.4454$ because these numbers $\notin\N$
 Nor is $f(x)$ defined for $x=0$ as $0\notin\N$
 Notice also $f(2) > f(1), f(3) > f(2)$ and so on. Which means, $f(x)$ is strictly increasing in $\N$. Hence, it looks as below
%
\begin{align}

\includegraphics[scale=1.5]{1427-C.svg}
\end{align}
%text
 \underline\text{The dotted line is the parabola} $\fx$%

